{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018Y6hAi7AvtiHK9RMChXeQ1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive final report:\n\n## Comprehensive Analysis of Cloche Web UI Architecture\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the Cloche project's web UI codebase. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### **1. Project Detail Page Implementation**\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1500 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (323 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (600 lines)\n\n**Key Handler Functions:**\n- `handleProjectDetail()` (lines 942-976) - Renders the project detail HTML page\n- `handleAPIProjectInfo()` (lines 978-1064) - Serves project metadata (Docker image, version, prompt file history)\n- `handleAPIPromptDiff()` (lines 1066-1095) - Serves git diffs for prompt file changes\n- `handleAPIWorkflows()` (lines 1097-1215) - Serves workflow definitions (container and host workflows)\n- `handleAPIStepContent()` (lines 1217-1298) - Serves step file contents\n\n---\n\n### **2. Workflow Steps Display & Click Handling**\n\n**Architecture:**\nThe project detail page uses a **DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) visualization** for workflows:\n\n**In `project_detail.html` (JavaScript section, lines 96-254):**\n- `loadWorkflows()` - Fetches workflow definitions via `/api/projects/{name}/workflows`\n- `switchLocation()` - Toggles between container and host workflows (lines 130-137)\n- `renderWorkflowTabs()` - Renders tabs for multiple workflows in same location (lines 139-159)\n- `showWorkflow()` - Generates SVG DAG with clickable step nodes (lines 168-254)\n- Steps are rendered as SVG rectangles with text and emoji icons:\n  - Agent steps: 🤖\n  - Workflow steps: 🔄\n  - Script/Prompt steps: 📋\n- **Click handler:** `onclick=\"openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)\"` (line 238)\n\n**Data Structure (from API response):**\n```javascript\n{\n  name: \"workflow-name\",\n  location: \"container\" | \"host\",\n  steps: [\n    {\n      name: \"step-name\",\n      type: \"agent\" | \"script\" | \"workflow\",\n      results: [\"result1\", \"result2\"],\n      config: {\n        prompt: \"...\",\n        command: \"...\",\n        script: \"...\",\n        workflow_name: \"...\"\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  wires: [\n    { from: \"step1\", result: \"success\", to: \"step2\" }\n  ],\n  entry_step: \"step-name\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **3. Prompt Steps File Content Display**\n\n**Drawer Component (lines 31-37 of `project_detail.html`):**\n```html\n<div class=\"drawer\" id=\"step-drawer\">\n  <div class=\"drawer-header\">\n    <span id=\"drawer-title\"></span>\n    <button class=\"drawer-close\" onclick=\"closeDrawer()\">&times;</button>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"drawer-body\" id=\"drawer-body\"></div>\n</div>\n```\n\n**Click Flow:**\n1. User clicks step node in DAG (line 238)\n2. `openDrawer(workflowName, stepName)` called (lines 256-289)\n3. Displays step metadata in drawer body (lines 262-276)\n4. Fetches content via `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` (line 279)\n5. Renders content in `<pre>` tag with HTML escaping (lines 282-288)\n\n**CSS Styling (lines 494-551 of `style.css`):**\n- Fixed position drawer that slides in from right (-420px to 0)\n- Full viewport height with scrollable body\n- Box shadow and smooth transition (0.25s ease)\n\n---\n\n### **4. Script Steps Handling**\n\n**In `handleAPIStepContent()` (lines 1217-1298):**\n\nScript steps are handled the same way as prompt steps. The function supports multiple step types:\n\n1. **Prompt steps:** `step.Config[\"prompt\"]` - reads the prompt file\n2. **Command steps:** `step.Config[\"command\"]` - displays the command\n3. **Script steps:** `step.Config[\"script\"]` - reads the script file\n4. **Workflow dispatch:** `step.Config[\"workflow_name\"]` - displays \"Dispatches workflow: {name}\"\n5. **Run steps:** `step.Config[\"run\"]` - reads the run reference\n\n**Special Handling:**\n- Uses `resolveFileRef()` function (lines 1302-1315) to handle `file(\"path\")` DSL syntax\n- If a step config value starts with `file(\"` and ends with `\")`, it reads the actual file from disk\n- Otherwise returns the config value as-is\n\nExample:\n```go\nif script := step.Config[\"script\"]; script != \"\" {\n    content, _ := resolveFileRef(script, dir)  // Resolves file(\"path\") or plain string\n    w.Write([]byte(content))\n    return\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **5. API Endpoints Summary**\n\n**All Step Content & File Serving Endpoints:**\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| `/api/projects/{name}/workflows` | GET | List all workflows (container & host) |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` | GET | **Step content (prompt/script/command)** |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/info` | GET | Project info (Docker image, version, prompt files) |\n| `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` | GET | Git diff for prompt files by SHA |\n| `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` | GET | Step execution output from run |\n| `/api/runs/{id}/stream` | GET | Live SSE stream of run logs |\n\n**Key Distinction:**\n- **`/api/projects/.../workflows/.../steps/.../content`** - Returns **step definition** file contents (what's in .cloche/)\n- **`/api/runs/.../steps/.../output`** - Returns **step execution** output from a specific run\n\n---\n\n### **6. File Resolution & Content Handling**\n\n**`resolveFileRef()` Function (lines 1302-1315):**\n```go\nfunc resolveFileRef(value, baseDir string) (string, error) {\n    if strings.HasPrefix(value, `file(\"`) && strings.HasSuffix(value, `\")`) {\n        path := value[6 : len(value)-2]  // Extract path from file(\"path\")\n        data, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(baseDir, path))\n        if err != nil {\n            return \"\", err\n        }\n        return string(data), nil\n    }\n    return value, nil\n}\n```\n\n**DSL Syntax Support:**\n- `prompt: file(\".cloche/prompts/my-prompt.md\")` - reads the file\n- `command: \"echo hello\"` - returns the command string directly\n- `script: file(\".cloche/scripts/setup.sh\")` - reads the script file\n\n---\n\n### **7. File Paths & Structure**\n\n**All relevant files:**\n\n1. **Handler:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n2. **Templates:**\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/layout.html` (base)\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (project page)\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (run execution page)\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (runs list)\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` (projects landing)\n3. **Styling:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n4. **Domain Models:** `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`, `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n5. **DSL Parser:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` (parses `.cloche/*.cloche` files)\n\n---\n\n### **8. Key JavaScript Functions in Project Detail Page**\n\n| Function | Lines | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `loadProjectInfo()` | 44-76 | Fetch project metadata |\n| `toggleDiff()` | 78-94 | Show/hide git diffs for prompt files |\n| `loadWorkflows()` | 99-128 | Load workflow definitions |\n| `switchLocation()` | 130-137 | Toggle container/host workflows |\n| `showWorkflow()` | 168-254 | Render SVG DAG with topological sort |\n| `openDrawer()` | 256-289 | Open right drawer with step details & content |\n| `closeDrawer()` | 291-293 | Close drawer |\n| `deleteAllContainers()` | 299-317 | Mass delete containers for project |\n\n---\n\n### **9. Current Implementation Gaps**\n\nThe code shows that:\n- **Prompt steps:** Content is fetched and displayed in drawer (fully implemented)\n- **Script steps:** Content is fetched and displayed in drawer (fully implemented)\n- **Command steps:** Content is displayed as-is in drawer\n- **Workflow dispatch steps:** Shows \"Dispatches workflow: {name}\" message\n- No special visual distinction between step types in the drawer UI\n\nAll file content is fetched client-side via `/api/projects/.../workflows/.../steps/.../content` and displayed in a right-sliding drawer with scrollable content."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a6ec9dfeee268839c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 65547\ntool_uses: 29\nduration_ms: 52054</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"375d7957-8c54-424f-9ca1-8e8227d8c94d","uuid":"67dc7b87-abe0-46dc-8db4-1055212c83c9","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the web UI codebase for the Cloche project. I need to understand:\n\n1. How the project detail page works - find all relevant files\n2. How workflow steps are displayed and how clicking on them works\n3. How prompt steps display their file contents when clicked\n4. How script steps are currently handled when clicked\n5. The API endpoints that serve file contents\n\nLook in directories like `internal/adapters/`, `cmd/`, and any web-related directories. Search for terms like \"prompt\", \"script\", \"step\", \"detail\", \"click\", \"contents\", \"file\", \"web\", \"template\", \"handler\", \"html\".\n\nBe very thorough - find all relevant files and report their paths and key code sections.","agentId":"a6ec9dfeee268839c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive final report:\n\n## Comprehensive Analysis of Cloche Web UI Architecture\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the Cloche project's web UI codebase. Here's the complete breakdown:\n\n### **1. Project Detail Page Implementation**\n\n**Files:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1500 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (323 lines)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web